"name": "2.50 V Rising Threshold Detector",
"description": "Comparator-based threshold detector that switches the output from LOW to HIGH when the input rises above 2.50 V. Uses an LM393 comparator, a 2.50 V reference divider, an output pull-up resistor, and local supply decoupling.",
