"notes": [
"The switching threshold is set by the divider: VREF = VDD × R2 / (R1 + R2). With R1 = R2 and VDD = 5.00 V, VREF = 2.50 V.",
"VIN is connected to the non-inverting input and VREF to the inverting input, so the output switches from LOW to HIGH when VIN rises above 2.50 V.",
"R3 provides the required pull-up for the LM393 open-collector output.",
"Use a regulated 5.00 V supply and precision divider resistors to keep the threshold within 2.50 V ±0.05 V.",
"U1 pin 7 (OUT2) is intentionally unconnected. U1 pins 5 and 6 are tied to GND so the unused comparator does not float."
]
